parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and catastrophic failure of Goodyear Marathon tires can lead to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, posing a significant risk to the safety of the occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Tires blow out at highway speeds
causing damage to the wheel well area and potentially leading to loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Goodyear Marathon tires can cause tread separation, blowouts, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The faulty suspension system can cause the RV to bounce excessively, leading to tire failure, electrical issues, and loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Excessive bouncing or bottoming out of the RV
tire bubbling or failure due to fatigue

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel hub axle assembly can cause the wheel to separate from the RV, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: and loss of control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden blowout of the Goodyear Marathon tire can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle or surrounding property, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: tire failure while driving at moderate to high speeds (60-65 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient wheel clearance can cause the tires to rub against the interior wheel well, leading to premature tire wear, reduced traction, and increased risk of tire failure, which can result in loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Tires rubbing against the interior wheel well
and increased risk of tire failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adhesive used to secure windows can cause them to become unsecured and fall out, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential injury to occupants.
symptoms: Windows becoming unsecured and falling out
loud noises or vibrations while driving
and damage to the vehicle's interior and exterior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Slider leakage and condensation can cause water damage, mold growth, and reduced structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: and water damage to the vehicle's interior and exterior.
